= LO hosts its 1971 congress

Boasting more than a million members, LO is an organizational behemoth representing nearly half the national workforce. For the first time in half a decade, the congress assembles, the athmosphere is electric.

The room goes quit as the chairman rises. He and the rest of the central commitee has advanced the program of 'Økonomisk Demokrati' (Economic Democracy, 'ØD'). A plan to legally acquire 51% of every single business in Denmark over a period of 10 years. According to the union leaders, the policy of ØD represents the culmination of 100 years of struggle.

Hands rise across the hall, a forest of consent. When they fall again, the verdict is clear: the program has carried, by an overwhelming majority.

