@ODmore
subtitle: Recommended for new players.

The policy of ØD is basically a plan to finance the legal seizing the means of production, the scheme seeks to achieve this by taking 5 percent of the wage sum each year in order to simply buy up all the businesses in Denmark with more than 6 employees. Key to this is the fact that this 5% wage sum would be an additional 5% provided by the businesses themselves.

The control of the stocks of these newly acquired businesses is then to be placed partly under the direct control of workers at the level of the individual firm and partly into a central fund. This central fund is to be jointly managed by a board appointed by the Danish folketing and the LO itself. 

In this way the plan is to take the first decisive step out of capitalism in order to create a new democratic economy.

